<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="woody climbers">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Woody climbers.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
Branchlets with prominent lenticels. Pith white, continuous through nodes. Tendrils leaf-opposed, mostly bifurcate to sometimes trifurcate, and lacking adhesive discs. Leaves alternate, petiolate, stipulate, pinnately to ternately bipinnately or sometimes tripinnately compound. Inflorescences bifurcately compound cymes, long peduncled, leaf-opposite. Flowers pedicellate, mostly bisexual; calyx saucer-like; corolla of 5 thick petals; stamens 5, opposite to petals; disc adnate to the base of the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="1" pageNumber="12" start="start">ovary</pageBreakToken>
; ovary 2-locular, style short, conical, stigma rounded. Fruit a berry, globose or subglobose, purple, blue or black, 1-4 seeded. Seeds obovoid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
